obs: " Four influenza B isolates were submitted for antigenic analysis; one resembled B/Ann Arbor/1/86, and the other was a related variant."
"Mentions both Yam and Vic viruses being characterized, but not their frequencies"

"Two distinct strains of influenza B virus, related to either the B/Victoria/2/87 or the B/Yamagata/16/88 and B/Panama/45/90 reference strains, have cocirculated in the world since 1988. Since October 1991, only two strains related to the B/Victoria/2/87 reference strain have been identified worldwide. Although relatively few influenza B viruses related to the B/Yamagata/16/88 and B/Panama/45/90 reference strains have been isolated, antigenic heterogeneity has been observed among them."
